1 SUMMARY
22 This resolution proposes to amend the Constitution of Maine to specify that only
33 citizens of the United States who are 18 years of age or older and who are residents of this
44 State are eligible to vote for Governor, Senators and Representatives and in any election in
55 the city, town or plantation where those citizens reside, except for persons under
66 guardianship for reasons of mental illness.
